{"questionId":"9067478","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Copper forms two chlorides, copper(I) chloride and copper(II) chloride.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Two electrolysis cells were assembled using graphite electrodes and connected in series as shown.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/0e2b920773da8385077e300e7d4c4df46d8aad7a.png\"></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Bubbles of gas were also observed at another electrode. Identify the electrode and the gas.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Electrode number (on diagram):</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Name of gas:&nbsp;</span></span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">«electrode» 3 <em><strong>AND</strong> </em>oxygen/O<sub>2</sub> ✔</span></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">NOTE:&nbsp;Accept chlorine/Cl<sub>2</sub>.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067478","referenceCode":"19N.2.hl.TZ0.6c(iii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Bubbles of gas were also observed at another electrode. Identify the electrode and the gas. Electrode number (on diagram): Name of gas:","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c(iii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 19: Redox processes","19.1 Electrochemical cells","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 19: Redox processes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}